1. Binance responds to OM flash crash: mainly caused by cross-trading platform liquidation, and will closely monitor the development of the situation;
2. OKX CEO Star: OM flash crash is a major scandal, and a full report will be prepared;
3. Janover, a US listed company, increased its holdings of 44,158 SOL, and the total holdings of SOL rose to 83,084;
4. Bitget responded to the campus ambassador controversy: always stick to the bottom line and will launch the "Green Campus Plan";
5. US Secretary of Commerce: China and the United States have had preliminary contact on tariff issues through intermediaries;
6. OM whale transferred more than US$90 million to OKX three days ago, and now has a floating loss of more than US$400 million;
7. Eric Trump: Bitcoin is one of the most valuable means of storage, with instant liquidity;
8. RFC market value exceeded US$100 million, and early large households made a floating profit of more than US$1.3 million;
9. The top five FARTCOIN addresses made a profit of more than US$8.9 million;
10. Bitcoin spot ETF had a net outflow last week 713 million USD, BlackRock Bitcoin ETF IBIT had the largest weekly net outflow of 342 million USD;
11. Metaplanet announced an increase of 319 Bitcoins.
